              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Inputs are 40px high, use square corners, and have 8px top/bottom and 12px left/right padding. Input labels are 16px bold. Default: white fill with black drop shadow (x6, y4, blur 0, spread 0). Focus: white fill with no shadow. Disabled: grey fill (#DCDCDC) and keeps the shadow. If an input has an icon, it sits on the right and uses a 16x16 size. Error messages sit to the right of the label in the same row, using 14px text and #FF6B6B. Textareas use the same visual rules with a minimum height of 80px. Checkboxes are 16x16, false = transparent fill, active = primary with black check icon. Switches are 24px high, false = transparent track, on = primary with black knob.",
